This article is a transcript of a press gaggle with Secretary of Education Arne Duncan aboard Air Force One. Secretary Duncan discusses the Race to the Top program and the importance of education in improving the economy. He also talks about the need for collaboration and innovation in the education system, as well as the importance of evaluating teachers based on student achievement. Secretary Duncan mentions that the grants for the Race to the Top program will start in January and discusses the high dropout rate in the U.S. He also emphasizes the need to increase the percentage of college graduates and mentions the importance of charter schools and their ability to innovate. Secretary Duncan concludes by stating that education is a civil rights issue and a fight for social justice.